<h1 >3.8.14.10 Qualification for Training Supplement</h1>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> The training supplement was a time limited measure available to eligible recipients who commenced an approved course between 1 July 2009 and 30 June 2011. The training supplement ceased to be available for new claimants commencing an approved course on or after 1 July 2011. The following information is for historical purposes only.</p>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>The training supplement was a temporary supplement paid to eligible income support recipients for approved courses commenced between 1 July 2009 and 30 June 2011.</p>
<h2>Qualification criteria</h2>
<p>To qualify for training supplement, a person was required to meet the following criteria:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Criterion</th>
<th scope="col">More Detail</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" scope="col">ALL of the following</th>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>Be in receipt of one of the following payments:</p>
<ul><li>newstart allowance, OR</li>
<li>parenting payment, AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>SS Guide <a href="../../2/1/10">3.2.1.10</a> Qualification for NSA</p>
<p><a href="../../5/1/10">3.5.1.10</a> Qualification Summary for PP</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>Have the following participation obligations:</p>
<ul><li>full-time, OR</li>
<li>part- time, AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p><a href="../../2/8">3.2.8</a> Mutual Obligation Requirements for NSA/YA Job Seekers</p>
<p><a href="../../2/11">3.2.11</a> Activity Test for NSA/YA - Exemptions</p>
<p><a href="../../5/1/160">3.5.1.160</a> When is a Job Plan Required? (PP)</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>A person MUST:</p>
<ul><li>NOT have completed Year 12 or an equivalent Certificate II qualification, OR</li>
<li>hold a trade or technical qualification which, if upgraded, would provide them with improved employment opportunity e.g. upgrading from Certificate II to Certificate III or IV qualification, OR</li>
<li>hold a trade or technical qualification in a field with poor employment prospects and could benefit by re-training in a new field at this level, AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>This topic.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>A person MUST:</p>
<ul><li>be participating in an approved course at the Certificate I to Certificate IV level (if participating in a Certificate I level course, it must be immediately followed by a Certificate II level course), AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>This topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>A person MUST:</p>
<ul><li>be fully meeting their participation or activity test requirements through participation in an approved course at the Certificate I to Certificate IV level (if participating in a Certificate I level course, it must be immediately followed by a Certificate II level course), AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>This topic.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<p>A person MUST:</p>
<ul><li>NOT be studying for or have been awarded a qualification accredited at diploma level or higher.</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>This topic.</p>
</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2>Suitable course to receive training supplement</h2>
<p>In order to receive training supplement a person must have been undertaking an approved training course for training supplement purposes. To be an approved training course, the course had to:</p>
<ul><li>be included in the person's <a href="../../../acronyms#epp" title="Employment pathway plan">EPP</a>, AND</li>
<li>last for no longer than 12 months, AND</li>
<li>be accredited at Certificate I, II, III, or IV level in the Australian Qualifications Framework (see note below), OR</li>
<li>be approved by a suitably delegated officer of Centrelink as being equivalent to a course accredited at any of those levels.</li>
</ul><p>The course must have led to a qualification that:</p>
<ul><li>was directly related to, and at a higher level than, the person's <a href="../../../acronyms#vet" title="Vocational education and training">VET</a> qualification within the Australian Qualifications Framework, OR</li>
<li>that enhanced the person's prospects of employment by allowing the person to gain skills in a trade or field of employment other than the trade or field of employment covered by the person's current VET qualification.</li>
</ul><p><strong>Note:</strong> The Australian Qualifications Framework has the meaning given by the <cite>Higher Education Support Act 2003</cite>.</p>
<p>For a Certificate I level course to meet eligibility, it must have been immediately followed by a Certificate II level course. The intention to enrol in the Certificate II level course should have been reflected in the person's EPP.</p>
<h2>Amount of study required for a person with full-time participation obligations</h2>
<p>In order to meet the study requirements to be eligible for training supplement, a person with full-time participation obligations must have met the definition of full-time student under SSAct section 569C. Under this section a person must undertake at least three-quarters of the normal amount of full-time study for the course.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 569C Full-time students</p>
</div>
<h2>Amount of study required for a person with a partial capacity to work OR for a principal carer of a child</h2>
<p>To meet the study requirements for a person with a partial capacity to work OR for a principal carer of at least one child, the person needed to undertake the number of hours of study required by their employment services provider or Centrelink in order to meet their participation requirements.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Matthew receives <a href="../../../acronyms#nsa" title="Newstart allowance">NSA</a> and has a partial capacity to work of 15-22 hours per week. Matthew has not completed his final year of secondary school and commences a 6-month Certificate II course which involves 10 face-to-face contact hours and 5 non-contact hours per week (a total of 15 hours per week). Matthew is fully meeting his requirements and also meets the qualification requirements for the training supplement.</p>
</div>
<h2><a href="../../../acronyms#pes" title="Pensioner education supplement">PES</a> &amp; the training supplement</h2>
<p>The training supplement was payable to a person who was in receipt of PES, provided the person met the qualification criteria for training supplement and the course they were undertaking was an approved course for training supplement purposes.</p>
<h2><a href="../../../acronyms#llns" title="Language, literacy and numeracy supplement">LLNS</a>, <a href="../../../acronyms#cps" title="Community Development Employment Projects (CDEP) Scheme Participant Supplement">CPS</a> &amp; <a href="../../../acronyms#apws" title="Approved program of work supplement">APWS</a> supplement NOT payable to a person receiving training supplement</h2>
<p>LLNS was not payable to a person if the person was in receipt of the training supplement.</p>
<p>CPS was not payable to a person if the person was in receipt of the training supplement.</p>
<p>A supplement for an APWS, such as <a href="../../../acronyms#wfd" title="Work for the Dole">WFD</a> or <a href="../../../acronyms#nwep" title="National Work Experience Programme">NWEP</a>, was not payable to a person if the person was in receipt of the training supplement.</p>
